	   <tr><td colspan=2>LOL, hehe, I have to agree that when a wizard is oom, we do look mighty sexy sitting there. As a wizzy, I get beat on alot more than other wizzys, mainly because I do NOT just nuke and med. All of the wizzys I know who do this are always causing serious downtime to the party, which just plain sucks. A wizzy should never go oom when fighting, or even under 60% (based on a small mana pool with no mana regen) when in normal group situations. I normally stay around 75-80% mana. And btw, dmg output is on a very small part of what a good player behind the wizard can do. The only foreseeable events in which one would occassionally go oom are on large raid bosses in which dmg output is primary, mana burning (duh), and when playing serious add control in order to save the party. Yes enc's are the best at add control for int casters, but a good wizzy can buy a ton of time for an enc to get those mezzes off. Stuns are god for groupings, if the mob can be stunned, and roots/snares are really great ways to play add control. Hell, I hardly ever throw a nuke out when grouping anymore, as most of the time I am stunning, dmg shielding, scouting, occassionally pulling, or by keeping and holding aggro while the rest of the party does the dmg. Stacking 25 seconds of stuns for 400m is an awesome way to hold aggro, be mana effecient, and keep the cleric fom all while everyone else does the dmg while I run around in little circles. And if the need should arise, I can wipe my aggro rather quickly and hand it off to someone else, or pull it really quickly to divert attention off of someone. And in some situations, using aoe's in a group are an awesome way to get the job done. The wizard just has to becareful to not pull aggro off the ONE mob the MA is fighting on. I do this by /assisting the MA and waiting till apx 75% to nuke with an aoe, followed by 2 succesfull concussions. Rinse and repeat as necessary. Rain based aoe's also do not like to work with this tactic, as the other mobs will aggro no matter how much aggro the MA is holding. Unfortunately, this does not work on some mobs and zones. It is high time that people realize an incredibly high dmg output and ports are not the only things wizzys are good for. Btw, I think this robe is great for all of the int casters, with non being above the rest in terms of need. All would put it to great use, and grats to those who obtain one.<br>&nbsp;<br>Reality is the fantasy world in which we live - J. Tracy<br>Vymdraven-Dark Elf Wizard<br>Bertox<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573242</a></td></tr>
